''This section includes some information from the [[American Community Survey|2022 American Community Survey]]''

At the [[2020 United States census|2020 census]] there were 1,392 people, 422 housing units and 540 households residing in the CDP. The racial makeup of the CDP was 58.26% [[Race and ethnicity in the United States census#2020 census|White]], 4.02% [[Race and ethnicity in the United States census#2020 census|African American]], 0.07% [[Race and ethnicity in the United States census#2020 census|Native American]], 23.13% [[Race and ethnicity in the United States census#2020 census|Asian]], 0.14% [[Race and ethnicity in the United States census#2020 census|Pacific Islander]], 2.44% from [[Race and ethnicity in the United States census#2020 census|other races]], and 11.93% from two or more races. [[Race and ethnicity in the United States census#2020 census|Hispanic]] or [[Race and ethnicity in the United States census#2020 census|Latino]] of any race was 6.82% of the population.<ref name=":0" />

Of the households, 23.2% were non-family households, 57.2% were married couple families, 9.4% were a male family householder with no spouse, and 10.2% were a female family householder with no spouse. The average family household had 3.06 people.<ref name=":0" />

The median age was 51.5, 21.1% of people were under the age of 18, and 6.1% were 65 years of age or older. The largest ancestry is the 10.9% who had [[Irish Americans|Irish ancestry]], 26.4% spoke a language other than [[English language|English]] at home, and 17.7% were born outside the United States, 94.2% of whom were [[Naturalized citizen of the United States|naturalized citizens]].<ref name=":0" />

The median income for a household in the CDP was over $250,000. 3.3% of the population were [[Veteran#United States|military veterans]], and 87.9% had a [[Bachelor's degree|batchelor's degree]] or [[Higher degree|higher]]. In the CDP 8.2% of the population was below the [[poverty line]], including 20.4% of those under the age of 18 and 29.2% of those aged 65 or over, with 0.4% of the population without [[Health insurance in the United States|health insurance]].<ref name=":0" />

